{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865594618,"sessionID":"ses_2862a2595ffenlv6DmPZBvKGaP","part":{"id":"prt_d79d67f08001ArrYPU9mE51rve","messageID":"msg_d79d676d6001Xs7MXC0WsSDDl6","sessionID":"ses_2862a2595ffenlv6DmPZBvKGaP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7ab8d97923c14ea4b1019117","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the DockerService encapsulation in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-024\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: DockerService is a core service class that encapsulates all Docker operations needed by the AgentCube CLI. It provides a clean abstraction layer over the Docker SDK, enabling the CLI to build, push, and manage container images without directly coupling to docker-py implementation details. The service handles Docker availability checks, image building with build args, image info retrieval, image pushing to registries with authentication, and image removal.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-024-001: Docker availability check\n25: \n26: The system SHALL verify Docker daemon is accessible before performing any Docker operations.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-A — Docker running returns true\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible via `docker.from_env()`\n31: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n32: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-B — Docker not running returns false\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running or not accessible\n37: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called and `docker.from_env()` raises `docker.errors.DockerException` or `docker.errors.APIError`\n38: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `False` and log a warning message\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-C — Docker not installed returns false\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** Docker is not installed or the Docker socket is unavailable\n43: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called and a `ConnectionError` or `FileNotFoundError` occurs\n44: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `False`\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### AR-024-002: Image building\n49: \n50: The system SHALL build container images from Dockerfiles using the Docker SDK.\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: AR-024-002-A — Build image with default tag\n53: \n54: - **GIVEN** Docker is running and valid `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, and `image_name` are provided\n55: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag=\"latest\")` is called\n56: - **THEN** the method SHALL build the image with tag `{image_name}:latest` using the Docker SDK\n57: - **AND** return a dict with keys: `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-024-002-B — Build image with custom tag\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** Docker is running and valid parameters with custom `tag` are provided\n62: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(..., tag=\"v1.0.0\")` is called\n63: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{image_name}:v1.0.0`\n64: - **AND** the returned dict SHALL reflect the custom tag\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-024-002-C — Build image with build args\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** Docker is running and `build_args` dict is provided (e.g., `{\"PROXY\": \"http://proxy:8080\"}`)\n69: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(..., build_args=build_args)` is called\n70: - **THEN** the Docker build SHALL pass the build args to the Docker daemon\n71: - **AND** the build SHALL succeed using the proxy settings\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-024-002-D — Build image failure\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** Docker is running but the Dockerfile is invalid or context is malformed\n76: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(...)` is called and the build fails\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `docker.errors.BuildError` or `docker.errors.APIError`\n78: - **AND** the error SHALL be propagated to the caller\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ### AR-024-003: Image info retrieval\n83: \n84: The system SHALL retrieve metadata about local Docker images.\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: AR-024-003-A — Get image info for existing image\n87: \n88: - **GIVEN** a built image exists locally with name `myagent:latest`\n89: - **WHEN** `DockerService.get_image_info(\"myagent:latest\")` is called\n90: - **THEN** the method SHALL return a dict containing `id`, `tags`, `size`, `created`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: AR-024-003-B — Get image info for non-existent image\n93: \n94: - **GIVEN** no local image with the given name exists\n95: - **WHEN** `DockerService.get_image_info(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n96: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `docker.errors.ImageNotFound`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: AR-024-003-C — Internal get image info with formatting\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** an image exists\n101: - **WHEN** `_get_image_info(image_name)` is called internally\n102: - **THEN** the method SHALL format the image size using `_format_size`\n103: - **AND** return a dict with human-readable size string\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ### AR-024-004: Image pushing\n108: \n109: The system SHALL push container images to remote registries with optional authentication.\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: AR-024-004-A — Push image without authentication\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** a local image `myagent:latest` exists and `registry_url` is provided without credentials\n114: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image(\"myagent:latest\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com\")` is called\n115: - **THEN** the method SHALL push the image without performing docker login\n116: - **AND** return a dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: AR-024-004-B — Push image with authentication\n119: \n120: - **GIVEN** a local image exists and valid `username`, `password` are provided\n121: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image(..., registry_url=\"registry.example.com\", username=\"user\", password=\"pass\")` is called\n122: - **THEN** the method SHALL call `_docker_login_sdk` to authenticate\n123: - **AND** retag the image if the registry URL differs from the current tag\n124: - **AND** push the image to the registry\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AR-024-004-C — Push image with custom target tag\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** local image `myagent:latest` and target tag `registry.example.com/myagent:v1.0.0`\n129: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image(\"myagent:latest\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com\", ...)` is called\n130: - **THEN** the image SHALL be retagged to `registry.example.com/myagent:latest` before push\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: AR-024-004-D — Push image failure\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** Docker is running but push fails (network issues, auth failure)\n135: - **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image(...)` is called and push fails\n136: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise the appropriate Docker error\n137: - **AND** the error SHALL be propagated to the caller\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ### AR-024-005: Image removal\n142: \n143: The system SHALL remove local Docker images.\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: AR-024-005-A — Remove existing image\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** a local image `myagent:latest` exists\n148: - **WHEN** `DockerService.remove_image(\"myagent:latest\")` is called\n149: - **THEN** the method SHALL remove the image from local storage\n150: - **AND** return `True`\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: AR-024-005-B — Remove non-existent image\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** no local image with the given name exists\n155: - **WHEN** `DockerService.remove_image(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n156: - **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning\n157: - **AND** return `False`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AR-024-005-C — Remove image failure\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** Docker is running but removal fails (e.g., image in use)\n162: - **WHEN** `DockerService.remove_image(...)` is called and removal fails\n163: - **THEN** the method SHALL log a warning\n164: - **AND** return `False`\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### AR-024-006: Size formatting utility\n169: \n170: The system SHALL format byte sizes into human-readable strings.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AR-024-006-A — Format bytes to KB\n173: \n174: - **GIVEN** a size of `1024` bytes\n175: - **WHEN** `DockerService._format_size(1024)` is called\n176: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"1.00 KB\"`\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: AR-024-006-B — Format bytes to MB\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** a size of `10485760` bytes (10 MB)\n181: - **WHEN** `DockerService._format_size(10485760)` is called\n182: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"10.00 MB\"`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AR-024-006-C — Format bytes to GB\n185: \n186: - **GIVEN** a size of `1073741824` bytes (1 GB)\n187: - **WHEN** `DockerService._format_size(1073741824)` is called\n188: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `\"1.00 GB\"`\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### AR-024-007: Docker login helper\n193: \n194: The system SHALL authenticate with Docker registries using the Docker SDK.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: AR-024-007-A — Login to registry\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** valid registry, username, and password\n199: - **WHEN** `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(registry=\"registry.example.com\", username=\"user\", password=\"pass\")` is called\n200: - **THEN** the method SHALL call the Docker SDK's login method\n201: - **AND** not raise any exception on success\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: AR-024-007-B — Login failure\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials\n206: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(...)` is called with wrong username/password\n207: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `docker.errors.APIError`\n208: - **AND** the error SHALL be propagated to the caller\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ### AR-024-008: Image tagging helper\n213: \n214: The system SHALL tag images with additional tags using the Docker SDK.\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: AR-024-008-A — Tag image\n217: \n218: - **GIVEN** source image `myagent:latest` and target `registry.example.com/myagent:v1.0.0`\n219: - **WHEN** `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(\"myagent:latest\", \"registry.example.com/myagent:v1.0.0\")` is called\n220: - **THEN** the Docker SDK SHALL create the new tag pointing to the source image\n221: - **AND** not raise any exception on success\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ### AR-024-009: Verbose logging support\n226: \n227: The system SHALL enable detailed logging when verbose mode is enabled.\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: AR-024-009-A — Verbose mode enables debug logging\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is instantiated\n232: - **WHEN** any method that produces logs is called\n233: - **THEN** the logging output SHALL include debug-level messages\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### AR-024-010: Integration with PackRuntime/BuildRuntime\n238: \n239: The system SHALL be used by runtime classes for Docker operations.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: AR-024-010-A — Pack validates Docker availability\n242: \n243: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube pack --build-mode local`\n244: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime` initiates build preparation\n245: - **THEN** it SHALL call `DockerService.check_docker_available()`\n246: - **AND** raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if unavailable\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-024-010-B — BuildRuntime builds image via DockerService\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** a valid packaged workspace and metadata\n251: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local(...)` is called\n252: - **THEN** it SHALL call `DockerService.build_image(...)` with the generated Dockerfile\n253: - **AND** return build result containing image info\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: AR-024-010-C — PublishRuntime pushes image via DockerService\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** successful local build with image\n258: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image(...)` is called\n259: - **THEN** it SHALL call `DockerService.push_image(...)` with registry credentials from metadata\n260: - **AND** return the pushed image identifier\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### AR-024-011: Error handling\n265: \n266: The system SHALL handle Docker-related errors gracefully.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: AR-024-011-A — Handle generic Docker exceptions\n269: \n270: - **GIVEN** an unexpected error occurs during Docker operation\n271: - **WHEN** the Docker SDK raises an unhandled exception type\n272: - **THEN** `DockerService` methods SHALL catch `Exception` as fallback\n273: - **AND** log the error message\n274: - **AND** re-raise or return `False` depending on method contract\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: AR-024-011-B — Handle timeout on push\n277: \n278: - **GIVEN** network is slow or registry is unresponsive\n279: - **WHEN** `push_image` exceeds default timeout\n280: - **THEN** the method SHALL raise `requests.exceptions.Timeout` or Docker timeout error\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [ ] AC001: DockerService.check_docker_available() returns correct boolean based on Docker daemon accessibility\n287: - [ ] AC002: DockerService.build_image() builds images with correct tags and returns build metadata\n288: - [ ] AC003: DockerService.build_image() passes build args to Docker daemon\n289: - [ ] AC004: DockerService.get_image_info() returns image metadata or raises on missing image\n290: - [ ] AC005: DockerService.push_image() pushes to registry with optional authentication\n291: - [ ] AC006: DockerService.push_image() handles image retagging for registry URLs\n292: - [ ] AC007: DockerService.remove_image() removes images and returns success status\n293: - [ ] AC008: DockerService._format_size() correctly formats bytes to KB/MB/GB\n294: - [ ] AC009: DockerService handles Docker exceptions and propagates appropriately\n295: - [ ] AC010: DockerService integrates with PackRuntime for Docker availability check\n296: - [ ] AC011: DockerService integrates with BuildRuntime for image building\n297: - [ ] AC012: DockerService integrates with PublishRuntime for image pushing\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## Architecture Notes\n302: \n303: ### Key Components\n304: \n305: | Component | Path | Description |\n306: |-----------|------|-------------|\n307: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Core Docker operations abstraction |\n308: | PackRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService for availability check |\n309: | BuildRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService.build_image() |\n310: | PublishRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Uses DockerService.push_image() |\n311: \n312: ### DockerService Class API\n313: \n314: ```python\n315: class DockerService:\n316:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n317:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n318:     def build_image(\n319:         self,\n320:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n321:         context_path: Path,\n322:         image_name: str,\n323:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n324:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n325:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n326:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n327:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n328:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n329:     def push_image(\n330:         self,\n331:         image_name: str,\n332:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n333:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n334:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n335:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n336:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n337:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n338:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ### Data Flow\n342: \n343: ```\n344: CLI Command (pack/build/publish)\n345:     │\n346:     ▼\n347: Runtime (PackRuntime/BuildRuntime/PublishRuntime)\n348:     │\n349:     ├──► DockerService.check_docker_available()\n350:     │\n351:     ├──► DockerService.build_image()\n352:     │\n353:     └──► DockerService.push_image()\n354:               │\n355:               ├──► DockerService._docker_login_sdk()\n356:               │\n357:               ├──► DockerService._tag_image_sdk()\n358:               │\n359:               └──► Docker SDK (docker-py)\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## References\n365: \n366: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — DockerService class definition (lines 216-243)\n367: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Docker integration requirements\n368: - Related: AR-020 (pack command), AR-021 (build command), AR-022 (publish command)\n369: - Related: AR-023 (invoke/status command)\n370: - Docker SDK: `docker>=6.0.0` from `pyproject.toml` dependencies\n\n(End of file - total 370 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the DockerService encapsulation in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-024\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nDockerService is a core service class that encapsulates all Docker operations needed by the AgentCube CLI. It provides a clean abstraction layer over the Docker SDK, enabling the CLI to build, push, and manage container images without directly coupling to docker-py implementation details. The service handles Docker availability checks, image building with build args, image info retrieval, image pushing to registries with authentication, and image removal.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775865594608,"end":1775865594616}}}}
